post_text:
From Mrs. DeFranco:
My first virtual learning assignment was for students to write me a friendly letter and email it to me with their address included. I then hand wrote personalized reply letters to each of my students in glitter pens and I cut out stickers to mail along with the letters to their houses. The students absolutely loved it! The feedback I received from parents was so heartfelt including parents telling me how happy the students were to receive a letter from me and that the letter I sent was the first letter the scholar had received.

Below are three of the letters and stickers I mailed to students.

Shanique Davis Speight is with Kelly Brunson and 45 others.
April 11 at 9:13 PM ·

Please Share Share Share!

A CONVERSATION WITH EXPERTS
Week 1: “Coronavirus in the Black Community”

A weekly forum with medical professionals & Experts to host conversations and present information to the public about COVID-19:

To highlight health disparities and social determinants of health that make the population more vulnerable
To address mental health in the Black community

To understand the impact on Black people who are on the frontlines (custodians, bus drivers, security guards, cleaning, crossing guards, etc.)

We are in this together!

TUNE IN A DIFFERENT TOPIC EVERY WEEK!

COVID-19 Impacts Everyone!!!!

Newark NJ Department of Public Safety
April 11 at 12:46 PM ·

Easter Bunny to Ride Through City on Fire Truck to Offer Holiday Smiles and Greetings to Children Sheltering Against Spread of COVID-19

Newark Mayor Ras J. Baraka and Public Safety Director Anthony F. Ambrose announce that the Easter Bunny will ride through the City on a fire truck offering holiday cheer and greetings to children sheltering against the spread of COVID-19 today, Saturday, April 11, 2020.

At 11 a.m., the Easter Bunny will greet children throughout the North Ward and South Ward until 12:30 p.m.

At 1 p.m., the lovable holiday bunny will greet children in the East Ward, Central Ward and West Ward until 2:30 p.m.

The Newark Department of Public Safety Wishes All a HAPPY EASTER!
